David Alpern:

I think that nicknames, as a global thing, are on the way out.  The existing
nicknames are just about all short forms of the official name (e.g., ISIF
for USC-ISIF.ARPA).  With domain style names it is not possible to have a
short form nickname that leaves out any of the structure.  There won't be
much advantage to having a nickname like "A.ISI.USC.EDU" instead of the full
name like "ALPHA.ISI.USC.EDU".

--jon.
